<title>BRAZIL: RESEARCH ALERT-Telerj downgraded.</title>
<headline>RESEARCH ALERT-Telerj downgraded.</headline>
<dateline>SAO PAULO 1997-06-02</dateline>
<text>
<p>Local investment bank Banco Icatu said Monday it has downgraded its rating for Brazilian state telecoms firm Telerj to market performer from outperformer following changes in the settlement rates companies must pay long-distance monopoly Embratel.</p>
<p>-- Bank analyst Marcelo Mollica said he also has maintained his outperformer rating on Telebras and its Telepar and Telesp units, as well as Rio Grande do Sul state-owned CRT.</p>
<p>-- He also reiterated his market-performer rating for Telemig, which along with Telerj is also a Telebras unit.</p>
</text>
